content:
Here's an example of how you can design a web interface using Angular to expose the room service reviews:

1. Create a new Angular project using the Angular CLI:
```javascript
ng new room-service-reviews
```
2. Generate a new component for displaying the reviews:
```
ng generate component room-service-reviews
```
3. In the `room-service-reviews.component.ts` file, you can define a property to store the room service reviews, and retrieve the data from a backend API in the `ngOnInit` lifecycle hook:
```typescript
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { HttpClient } from '@angular/common/http';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-room-service-reviews',
  templateUrl: './room-service-reviews.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./room-service-reviews.component.css']
})
export class RoomServiceReviewsComponent implements OnInit {
  reviews: any;

  constructor(private http: HttpClient) { }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.http.get('http://localhost:3000/reviews').subscribe(reviews => {
      this.reviews = reviews;
    });
  }
}
```
4. In the `room-service-reviews.component.html` file, you can use Angular's template syntax to loop over the `reviews` property and display the information for each review:
```css
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Hotel</th>
      <th>Date</th>
      <th>Rating</th>
      <th>Review</th>
      <th>Time to Deliver</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr *ngFor="let review of reviews">
      <td>{{ review.hotel.name }}</td>
      <td>{{ review.date }}</td>
      <td>{{ review.rating }}</td>
      <td>{{ review.review }}</td>
      <td>{{ review.time_to_deliver }}</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```
5. Finally, you can add the `RoomServiceReviewsComponent` to the module's declarations and the `AppComponent` template to display the reviews on the main page:
```python
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { HttpClientModule } from '@angular/common/http';

import { AppComponent } from './app.component';
import { RoomServiceReviewsComponent } from './room-service-reviews/room-service-reviews.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    AppComponent,
    RoomServiceReviewsComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    HttpClientModule
  ],
  providers: [],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule { }
```

